    <item>
      <title>A Child&#39;s View of War</title>
      <link>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/a-childs-view-of-war/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 May 2017 21:48:55 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/a-childs-view-of-war/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There was a shelter in the yard&lt;br /&gt;
Of corrugated iron&lt;br /&gt;
The government provided it&lt;br /&gt;
To give us safe environs.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Fun With Breast Cancer</title>
      <link>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/fun-with-breast-cancer/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2017 22:07:52 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/fun-with-breast-cancer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m sitting on the table&lt;br /&gt;
And the doctor looks at me&lt;br /&gt;
The biopsies are back,&lt;br /&gt;
And you do have the big C.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Reflections on Chair Yoga</title>
      <link>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/reflections-on-chair-yoga/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2017 12:57:36 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://pessimisticpoems.com/blog/reflections-on-chair-yoga/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;My chair yoga is for those&lt;br /&gt;
who can no longer touch their toes.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We hobble in on cane and brace&lt;br /&gt;
And sit in our allotted place.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
